attributes.background:
With today's technology, millions of man-hours of intelligence can be put towards solving our nation's challenges, large and small - for almost no cost.

A wiki-based policy website would: 
1) Rally the experience and expertise of the country towards national and local policy challenges; 
2) Provide transparency so constituents can follow the formulation of policy ideas that affect them;
3) Function as added public consultation; 
4) Empower local interests;
5) Stimulate citizenship.

The website would function with the same rules and etiquette as Wikipedia: 
•  Assertions must be backed up by facts; 
•  Aggressive behaviour, prejudice, and vandalism would not be tolerated; 
•  Everyone can make edits, reverse changes, add new policy areas; etc.

We cannot underestimate the good will and will power of our citizens. Any forward-looking government would do well to harness the power of "citizen-sourcing" and unleash its strengths for all society to benefit.
